-- Italian Bonds Gain; Two-Year Yield Drops to Lowest in a Week
-- B y   D a v i d   G o o d m a n
-- 2012-08-29T13:35:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-29/italian-bonds-gain-two-year-yield-drops-to-lowest-in-a-week.html
Italian securities advanced, pushing
the yield on the two-year note to the lowest in a week.  The  rate  fell nine basis points to 2.96 percent as of 2:33
p.m. London time. That’s the lowest since Aug. 22.  The nation’s 10-year yield slipped five basis points to
5.78 percent after earlier rising to 5.89 percent, the highest
since Aug. 14. Italy aims to sell a combined 7.5 billion euros
of debt due in 2017 and 2022 tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Goodman in London at 
